<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1882-03-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1882-03-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="109" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d109">
                    <head>No. 109.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Lowell</persName></hi>.</head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1882-03-03"><hi rend="italic">March</hi> 3,
                            1882</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>[States that the cases of our citizens under arrest in Ireland is the
                        occasion of inquiry in the House of Representatives, and instructs Mr.
                        Lowell to use all diligence in regard to the late cases, especially of Hart
                        and McSweeny, and to report his action by cable.]</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>